ngton Post) exposes the human cost of promoting pharmaceuticals for off-label uses. Charles Duhigg and David Barboza (New York Times) investigate Apple's unethical labor practices in China. Max Abelson (Bloomberg) reports on Wall Street's amusing reaction to the diminishing annual bonus. Mina Kimes (Fortune) recounts the grisly story of a company's illegal testing—and misuse—of a medical device for profit, and Jeff Tietz (Rolling Stone) composes one of the most poignant and comprehensive portraits of the financial crisis's dissolution of the American middle class.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aBusiness enterprisesxCorrupt practices. 0aBusiness. 0aBusinesspeople. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Business Writing.2bisacsh1 aAngell, Marcia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarrett, Rick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeck, Chad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBernstein, Jake, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBolt, Adam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuffett, Warren, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurke, Doris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarney, Brian M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarter, Zach, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChafkin, Max, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChittum, Ryan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCollins, Lauren, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavies, Nick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEisinger, Jesse, econtributor.4ctb4http